HB 1158 Original 2026 Regular Session Butler
Abstract: Requires that all warnings and caution statements on the pesticide match exactly
the safety warnings on the United States Environmental Protection Agency
(EPA)-registered product label and not be changed in any significant way.
Present law requires that each application for initial registration or re-registration of a
pesticide with a changed label include two complete copies of the pesticide labeling,
including directions for use and all warnings or caution statements.
Proposed law retains present law and further requires that all warnings or caution statements
match the EPA-registered product label and not be materially altered.
(Amends R.S. 3:3221(B)(3)(f))
